==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|punischen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|punire||to inflict punishment upon|lang=la}}, from {{term|poena||punishment, penalty}}; see {{term|pain}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈpʌnɪʃ/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/"pVnIS/}}
* {{audio|en-us-punish.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|punish|es}}

# To [[cause]] to [[suffer]] for [[crime]] or [[misconduct]], to [[administer]] [[disciplinary]] [[action]].
# To cause great [[harm]] to. (''a punishing blow'')
# To [[dumb down]] severely or to the point of uselessness or near-uselessness.

